file.name: googleapis.com-adsensehost-v4.1-swagger.yaml
file.content:
openapi: 3.0.0
info:
  contact:
    name: Google
    url: https://google.com
  description: Generates performance reports, generates ad codes, and provides publisher
    management capabilities for AdSense Hosts.
  license:
    name: Creative Commons Attribution 3.0
    url: http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/
  termsOfService: https://developers.google.com/terms/
  title: AdSense Host
  version: v4.1
  x-apiClientRegistration:
    url: https://console.developers.google.com
  x-logo:
    url: https://www.google.com/images/branding/googlelogo/2x/googlelogo_color_272x92dp.png
  x-origin:
    - converter:
        url: https://github.com/lucybot/api-spec-converter
        version: 2.7.31
      format: google
      url: https://www.googleapis.com/discovery/v1/apis/adsensehost/v4.1/rest
      version: v1
  x-preferred: true
  x-providerName: googleapis.com
  x-serviceName: adsensehost
externalDocs:
  url: https://developers.google.com/adsense/host/
tags:
  - name: accounts
  - name: adclients
  - name: associationsessions
  - name: customchannels
  - name: reports
  - name: urlchannels
paths:
  /accounts:
    get:
      description: List hosted accounts associated with this AdSense account by ad client
        id.
      operationId: adsensehost.accounts.list
      parameters:
        - description: Ad clients to list accounts for.
          in: query
          name: filterAdClientId
          required: true
          explode: true
          schema:
            type: array
            items:
              type: string
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/Accounts"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
          Oauth2c:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
      tags:
        - accounts
    parameters:
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/alt"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/fields"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/key"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/oauth_token"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/prettyPrint"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/quotaUser"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/userIp"
  "/accounts/{accountId}":
    get:
      description: Get information about the selected associated AdSense account.
      operationId: adsensehost.accounts.get
      parameters:
        - description: Account to get information about.
          in: path
          name: accountId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/Account"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
          Oauth2c:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
      tags:
        - accounts
    parameters:
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/alt"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/fields"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/key"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/oauth_token"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/prettyPrint"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/quotaUser"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/userIp"
  "/accounts/{accountId}/adclients":
    get:
      description: List all hosted ad clients in the specified hosted account.
      operationId: adsensehost.accounts.adclients.list
      parameters:
        - description: Account for which to list ad clients.
          in: path
          name: accountId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: The maximum number of ad clients to include in the response, used
            for paging.
          in: query
          name: maxResults
          schema:
            type: integer
            minimum: 0
            maximum: 10000
        - description: A continuation token, used to page through ad clients. To retrieve
            the next page, set this parameter to the value of "nextPageToken"
            from the previous response.
          in: query
          name: pageToken
          schema:
            type: string
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/AdClients"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
          Oauth2c:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
      tags:
        - accounts
    parameters:
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/alt"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/fields"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/key"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/oauth_token"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/prettyPrint"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/quotaUser"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/userIp"
  "/accounts/{accountId}/adclients/{adClientId}":
    get:
      description: Get information about one of the ad clients in the specified publisher's
        AdSense account.
      operationId: adsensehost.accounts.adclients.get
      parameters:
        - description: Account which contains the ad client.
          in: path
          name: accountId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: Ad client to get.
          in: path
          name: adClientId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/AdClient"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
          Oauth2c:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
      tags:
        - accounts
    parameters:
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/alt"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/fields"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/key"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/oauth_token"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/prettyPrint"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/quotaUser"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/userIp"
  "/accounts/{accountId}/adclients/{adClientId}/adunits":
    get:
      description: List all ad units in the specified publisher's AdSense account.
      operationId: adsensehost.accounts.adunits.list
      parameters:
        - description: Account which contains the ad client.
          in: path
          name: accountId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: Ad client for which to list ad units.
          in: path
          name: adClientId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: "Whether to include inactive ad units. Default: true."
          in: query
          name: includeInactive
          schema:
            type: boolean
        - description: The maximum number of ad units to include in the response, used for
            paging.
          in: query
          name: maxResults
          schema:
            type: integer
            minimum: 0
            maximum: 10000
        - description: A continuation token, used to page through ad units. To retrieve the
            next page, set this parameter to the value of "nextPageToken" from
            the previous response.
          in: query
          name: pageToken
          schema:
            type: string
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/AdUnits"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
          Oauth2c:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
      tags:
        - accounts
    parameters:
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/alt"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/fields"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/key"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/oauth_token"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/prettyPrint"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/quotaUser"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/userIp"
    patch:
      description: Update the supplied ad unit in the specified publisher AdSense account.
        This method supports patch semantics.
      operationId: adsensehost.accounts.adunits.patch
      parameters:
        - description: Account which contains the ad client.
          in: path
          name: accountId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: Ad client which contains the ad unit.
          in: path
          name: adClientId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: Ad unit to get.
          in: query
          name: adUnitId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
      requestBody:
        $ref: "#/components/requestBodies/AdUnit"
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/AdUnit"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
          Oauth2c:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
      tags:
        - accounts
    post:
      description: Insert the supplied ad unit into the specified publisher AdSense account.
      operationId: adsensehost.accounts.adunits.insert
      parameters:
        - description: Account which will contain the ad unit.
          in: path
          name: accountId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: Ad client into which to insert the ad unit.
          in: path
          name: adClientId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
      requestBody:
        $ref: "#/components/requestBodies/AdUnit"
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/AdUnit"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
          Oauth2c:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
      tags:
        - accounts
    put:
      description: Update the supplied ad unit in the specified publisher AdSense account.
      operationId: adsensehost.accounts.adunits.update
      parameters:
        - description: Account which contains the ad client.
          in: path
          name: accountId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: Ad client which contains the ad unit.
          in: path
          name: adClientId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
      requestBody:
        $ref: "#/components/requestBodies/AdUnit"
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/AdUnit"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
          Oauth2c:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
      tags:
        - accounts
  "/accounts/{accountId}/adclients/{adClientId}/adunits/{adUnitId}":
    delete:
      description: Delete the specified ad unit from the specified publisher AdSense
        account.
      operationId: adsensehost.accounts.adunits.delete
      parameters:
        - description: Account which contains the ad unit.
          in: path
          name: accountId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: Ad client for which to get ad unit.
          in: path
          name: adClientId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: Ad unit to delete.
          in: path
          name: adUnitId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/AdUnit"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
          Oauth2c:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
      tags:
        - accounts
    get:
      description: Get the specified host ad unit in this AdSense account.
      operationId: adsensehost.accounts.adunits.get
      parameters:
        - description: Account which contains the ad unit.
          in: path
          name: accountId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: Ad client for which to get ad unit.
          in: path
          name: adClientId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: Ad unit to get.
          in: path
          name: adUnitId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/AdUnit"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
          Oauth2c:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
      tags:
        - accounts
    parameters:
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/alt"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/fields"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/key"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/oauth_token"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/prettyPrint"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/quotaUser"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/userIp"
  "/accounts/{accountId}/adclients/{adClientId}/adunits/{adUnitId}/adcode":
    get:
      description: Get ad code for the specified ad unit, attaching the specified host
        custom channels.
      operationId: adsensehost.accounts.adunits.getAdCode
      parameters:
        - description: Account which contains the ad client.
          in: path
          name: accountId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: Ad client with contains the ad unit.
          in: path
          name: adClientId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: Ad unit to get the code for.
          in: path
          name: adUnitId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: Host custom channel to attach to the ad code.
          in: query
          name: hostCustomChannelId
          explode: true
          schema:
            type: array
            items:
              type: string
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/AdCode"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
          Oauth2c:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
      tags:
        - accounts
    parameters:
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/alt"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/fields"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/key"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/oauth_token"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/prettyPrint"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/quotaUser"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/userIp"
  "/accounts/{accountId}/reports":
    get:
      description: Generate an AdSense report based on the report request sent in the query
        parameters. Returns the result as JSON; to retrieve output in CSV format
        specify "alt=csv" as a query parameter.
      operationId: adsensehost.accounts.reports.generate
      parameters:
        - description: Hosted account upon which to report.
          in: path
          name: accountId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: Dimensions to base the report on.
          in: query
          name: dimension
          explode: true
          schema:
            type: array
            items:
              type: string
        - description: End of the date range to report on in "YYYY-MM-DD" format, inclusive.
          in: query
          name: endDate
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: Filters to be run on the report.
          in: query
          name: filter
          explode: true
          schema:
            type: array
            items:
              type: string
        - description: Optional locale to use for translating report output to a local
            language. Defaults to "en_US" if not specified.
          in: query
          name: locale
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: The maximum number of rows of report data to return.
          in: query
          name: maxResults
          schema:
            type: integer
            minimum: 0
            maximum: 50000
        - description: Numeric columns to include in the report.
          in: query
          name: metric
          explode: true
          schema:
            type: array
            items:
              type: string
        - description: The name of a dimension or metric to sort the resulting report on,
            optionally prefixed with "+" to sort ascending or "-" to sort
            descending. If no prefix is specified, the column is sorted
            ascending.
          in: query
          name: sort
          explode: true
          schema:
            type: array
            items:
              type: string
        - description: Start of the date range to report on in "YYYY-MM-DD" format,
            inclusive.
          in: query
          name: startDate
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: Index of the first row of report data to return.
          in: query
          name: startIndex
          schema:
            type: integer
            minimum: 0
            maximum: 5000
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/Report"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
          Oauth2c:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
      tags:
        - accounts
    parameters:
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/alt"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/fields"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/key"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/oauth_token"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/prettyPrint"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/quotaUser"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/userIp"
  /adclients:
    get:
      description: List all host ad clients in this AdSense account.
      operationId: adsensehost.adclients.list
      parameters:
        - description: The maximum number of ad clients to include in the response, used
            for paging.
          in: query
          name: maxResults
          schema:
            type: integer
            minimum: 0
            maximum: 10000
        - description: A continuation token, used to page through ad clients. To retrieve
            the next page, set this parameter to the value of "nextPageToken"
            from the previous response.
          in: query
          name: pageToken
          schema:
            type: string
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/AdClients"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
          Oauth2c:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
      tags:
        - adclients
    parameters:
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/alt"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/fields"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/key"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/oauth_token"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/prettyPrint"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/quotaUser"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/userIp"
  "/adclients/{adClientId}":
    get:
      description: Get information about one of the ad clients in the Host AdSense account.
      operationId: adsensehost.adclients.get
      parameters:
        - description: Ad client to get.
          in: path
          name: adClientId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/AdClient"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
          Oauth2c:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
      tags:
        - adclients
    parameters:
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/alt"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/fields"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/key"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/oauth_token"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/prettyPrint"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/quotaUser"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/userIp"
  "/adclients/{adClientId}/customchannels":
    get:
      description: List all host custom channels in this AdSense account.
      operationId: adsensehost.customchannels.list
      parameters:
        - description: Ad client for which to list custom channels.
          in: path
          name: adClientId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: The maximum number of custom channels to include in the response,
            used for paging.
          in: query
          name: maxResults
          schema:
            type: integer
            minimum: 0
            maximum: 10000
        - description: A continuation token, used to page through custom channels. To
            retrieve the next page, set this parameter to the value of
            "nextPageToken" from the previous response.
          in: query
          name: pageToken
          schema:
            type: string
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/CustomChannels"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
          Oauth2c:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
      tags:
        - customchannels
    parameters:
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/alt"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/fields"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/key"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/oauth_token"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/prettyPrint"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/quotaUser"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/userIp"
    patch:
      description: Update a custom channel in the host AdSense account. This method
        supports patch semantics.
      operationId: adsensehost.customchannels.patch
      parameters:
        - description: Ad client in which the custom channel will be updated.
          in: path
          name: adClientId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: Custom channel to get.
          in: query
          name: customChannelId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
      requestBody:
        $ref: "#/components/requestBodies/CustomChannel"
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/CustomChannel"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
          Oauth2c:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
      tags:
        - customchannels
    post:
      description: Add a new custom channel to the host AdSense account.
      operationId: adsensehost.customchannels.insert
      parameters:
        - description: Ad client to which the new custom channel will be added.
          in: path
          name: adClientId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
      requestBody:
        $ref: "#/components/requestBodies/CustomChannel"
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/CustomChannel"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
          Oauth2c:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
      tags:
        - customchannels
    put:
      description: Update a custom channel in the host AdSense account.
      operationId: adsensehost.customchannels.update
      parameters:
        - description: Ad client in which the custom channel will be updated.
          in: path
          name: adClientId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
      requestBody:
        $ref: "#/components/requestBodies/CustomChannel"
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/CustomChannel"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
          Oauth2c:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
      tags:
        - customchannels
  "/adclients/{adClientId}/customchannels/{customChannelId}":
    delete:
      description: Delete a specific custom channel from the host AdSense account.
      operationId: adsensehost.customchannels.delete
      parameters:
        - description: Ad client from which to delete the custom channel.
          in: path
          name: adClientId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: Custom channel to delete.
          in: path
          name: customChannelId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/CustomChannel"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
          Oauth2c:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
      tags:
        - customchannels
    get:
      description: Get a specific custom channel from the host AdSense account.
      operationId: adsensehost.customchannels.get
      parameters:
        - description: Ad client from which to get the custom channel.
          in: path
          name: adClientId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
        - description: Custom channel to get.
          in: path
          name: customChannelId
          required: true
          schema:
            type: string
      responses:
        "200":
          description: Successful response
          content:
            "*/*":
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/CustomChannel"
      security:
        - Oauth2:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
          Oauth2c:
            - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adsensehost
      tags:
        - customchannels
    parameters:
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/alt"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/fields"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/key"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/oauth_token"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/prettyPrint"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/quotaUser"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/userIp"
  "/adclients/{adClientId}/urlchannels":
    get:
      description: List all host URL channels in the host AdSense account.
      operationId: adsensehost.urlchannels.list

servers:

components:

      description: Data format for the response.

      in: query

        type: string
